news.title: IHCL plans to add over 30 new hotels in FY26
news.para: On the number of rooms to be added through the new properties in FY26, Chhatwal said it could be around 4,500 rooms at an average of 150 rooms per new hotel.

news.title: Ambuja Cements reassigns Ajay Kapur as managing director for two years
news.para: Kapur, who has spent three decades working in the cement, construction, power and heavy metals sectors, has been appointed for a two-year term while Bahety will serve as CEO for three years.

news.title: Muda plans to build five-star hotel under PPP in west Mysuru
news.para: Besides, the urban body has reserved Rs 7.7 crore to prepare DPAR for 105km six-lane peripheral road of 45m width. The commissioner said the peripheral road is a requirement given the growing vehicle population which is currently eight lakh.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government constitutes DLACs to give land to the poor
news.para: Taking the vast available land in several districts into consideration, the govt is contemplating to launch the assignment of land to the landless agriculture poor.

news.title: Brigade Group to jointly develop land parcel in Mysuru
news.para: The proposed project will feature a residential development of approximately 0.45 million sq ft, with a gross development value (GDV) of ₹300 crore.

news.title: Gurugram: MCG reduces property ID objections from 11,029 to 3,135 till March 26
news.para: MCG data shows that of the 6.9 lakh properties registered in the city, objections were received from 3.6 lakh property owners since 2022.

news.title: Bhopal district committee discusses objections to 18% hike in property guideline rates
news.para: In the original plan, the district evaluation committee had proposed an average 18% increase in rates at more than 1,200 locations in Bhopal, with the maximum increase proposed in the outskirts of the city.

news.title: Nashik civic body receives over 1,200 building plan proposals offline in 10 days
news.para: Civic body chief Manisha Khatri had given permission to the department for offline submission and approval of the building plan proposals for 10 days up to March 26.

news.title: Four days left to avail OTS for 90% waiver on property tax interest in Hyderabad: GHMC
news.para: GHMC commissioner K Ilambarithi said that property tax can be paid online, through citizen service centres and e-Seva Kendras in the circle and headquarters, which will operate from 8 am to 11 pm.

news.title: Over 4,000 Lucknow development body's tenants to get ownership
news.para: Of these, 1,355 residential and 616 commercial properties are already registered. However, 1,410 residential and 364 commercial properties are yet to be registered.

news.title: Supreme Court stays probe against Madhya Pradesh RERA chief till April 2
news.para: A Bench led by Justice JB Pardiwala sought response from the Madhya Pradesh government and others on a petition filed by Shrivastava and Madhya Pradesh Real Estate Regulatory Authority and posted the matter for further hearing on April 2.

news.title: Owners giving up land for civic projects in Maharashtra may get compulsory acquisition: Revenue minister
news.para: As per the prevailing practice, willing landowners are receiving less compensation and also need to pay income tax on the amount received.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong fell 0.9% in February 2025
news.para: Private home prices fell 0.9% in February from the month before, following a revised 0.7% decline in January, data from the Rating and Valuation Department showed.

news.title: Office leasing in India rise 15% to 159 lakh sq ft in Q1 FY25: Colliers
news.para: As per the data, the gross leasing of office space in Bengaluru increased 13 per cent to 45 lakh square feet in the current quarter from 40 lakh square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: Housing sales in India may fall 28 % in Q1 FY25: Anarock
news.para: As per the data, the total housing sales are estimated at 93,280 units in January-March 2025, a 28 per cent decline from 1,30,170 units in the year-ago period.

news.title: US-based CoStar raises acquisition bid for Domain Holdings to $1.76 billion
news.para: CoStar sweetened its offer to A$4.43 per share on a "best and final" basis, Domain said in a statement, representing a 5.5% premium to its initial proposal of A$4.20.

news.title: CREDAI Andhra Pradesh applauds govt’s decision to abolish NALA Act
news.para: The move follows persistent advocacy by CREDAI Andhra Pradesh, which had highlighted the burden imposed by high land conversion charges on both developers and the general public.

news.title: Mohali civic body exceeds its property tax collection target by 10% in FY 2024-25
news.para: Looking ahead, the proposed budget for fiscal year 2025-26 projects property tax as the highest revenue source, with an estimated collection of Rs 55 crore. This marks a significant rise from Rs 45 crore collected in 2024-25.
